You can programmatically trigger the toast by using React&#39;s useEffect hook. The useEffect hook works well for any side effects, such as fetching data or DOM manipulations.
```
 const toast = useToast();

  useEffect(() =&gt; {
    // Show toast every 5 seconds.
    setInterval(() =&gt; {
      toast({
        title: &quot;Current Time.&quot;,
        description: `Time ${new Date()}`,
        status: &quot;success&quot;,
        duration: 5000,
        isClosable: true
      });
    }, 5000);
  }, []); // Passing in empty array so this will only get called on mount
```
