If you use a while loop, you need to have a criteria for it to stop iteration otherwise it continues to infinity. You can either use a for loop that ends at 25 or whatever number is needed or use a while loop with variable that will be used to terminate the loop. You created an infinite loop and it breaks after producing one iteration. 

    count = 0
    while (count &lt; 9):
       print &#39;The count is:&#39;, count
       count = count + 1

Second, break tells python to exit the loop entirely. If you use a break it will tell python to stop running the loop. 

If you want to format a string for printing a stylish output, you need to use string formatting where you either use format() or the newer f-strings

