answers.body_markdown:
Mongodb drive official [doc][1] said that `close`  function is like a callback style function, it just return a dummy Promise if no callback passed. Source code [lib/mongo_client.js, line 310][2] . This mean the `await` keyword does not help wait until the connection is disconnected.

```
await mongoConfiguration.disconnectClient();
expect(client.isConnected()).equals(false);
```

`client.isConnected()` executes immediately after `await mongoConfiguration.disconnectClient();` line, while ` await this._client.close();` still did not &quot;finish&quot;, then `client.isConnected()` will be `true`.

Solution, convert `this._client.close()` into a promise.


```
  public disconnectClient = async () =&gt; {
    try {
      await new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; { // wait until it finish the `close` job
        this._client.close((error) =&gt; {
          if (error) {
            return reject(error);
          }
          resolve();
        });
      });
      console.log(&#39;Connection to MongoDB closed&#39;);
    } catch (err) {
      throw err;
    }
  };
```

 


 


  [1]: https://mongodb.github.io/node-mongodb-native/3.0/api/MongoClient.html#close
  [2]: https://mongodb.github.io/node-mongodb-native/3.0/api/lib_mongo_client.js.html

